JaCoCo (Java Code Coverage) is a popular tool for measuring code coverage in Java applications. It instruments Java bytecode, providing metrics such as line, branch, and method coverage during testing. Integrated with Maven, Gradle, and Ant, it seamlessly fits into the build process. JaCoCo generates detailed reports in formats like HTML, XML, and CSV, aiding developers in identifying untested or under-tested code areas. With line-by-line and branch coverage analysis, it highlights executed and unexecuted code paths. The tool is compatible with various IDEs, providing developers with insights into code coverage directly within their development environment. Regular usage helps improve software quality and reliability by ensuring comprehensive test coverage.
